===Tom Izzo era (1995âpresent)=== Since 1995, the team has been coached by [[Tom Izzo]], who has an overall record of 383â161 as head coach at Michigan State.<ref>MSU Spartans.com [http://msuspartans.collegesports.com/sports/m-baskbl/mtt/izzo_tom00.html Player Bio: Tom Izzo].</ref> Izzo coached the Spartans to their second national championship in 2000 with an 89â76 victory over [[Florida Gators men's basketball|Florida]]. Izzo has guided the Spartans to six of twelve NCAA [[Final Four]]s from 1999 to 2010, an accomplishment unmatched by any other college basketball program during that span. The coach has also appeared in a postseason tournament every year he has headed the MSU basketball program.
Izzo has also received numerous awards including the 1998 [[Associated Press]] National Coach of the Year, the 1998 Basketball News National Coach of the Year, the 1998 United States Basketball Writers Association [[Henry Iba]] Coach of the Year Award, the 1998 [[Big Ten Conference]] Coach of the Year, the 1998 Basketball Times Mideast Coach of the Year, the 1999 Basketball News Coach of the Year Award, the 2001 National Association of Basketball Coaches Coach of the Year Award, the 2005 Clair Bee Award<ref>[http://msuspartans.cstv.com/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/111106aaa.html Men's Basketball Returns To Action Against The Citadel :: Spartans look for third victory in five days<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> and the 2009 Big Ten Conference Coach of the Year.
Izzo has also helped his assistants secure head coaching jobs across the basketball world. Five current Division I head coaches served as assistants under Izzo: [[Brian Gregory]] at [[Georgia Tech men's basketball|Georgia Tech]], [[Tom Crean (coach)|Tom Crean]] at [[Indiana Hoosiers men's basketball|Indiana]], [[Stan Heath]] at [[South Florida men's basketball|South Florida]], [[Mark Montgomery]] at [[Northern Illinois University|Northern Illinois]], and [[Doug Wojcik]] at [[Tulsa Golden Hurricanes men's basketball|Tulsa]]. Current assistant coach [[Mike Garland]] spent three seasons as head coach at [[Cleveland State Vikings men's basketball|Cleveland State]] following an initial seven-year stint at MSU. Former MSU assistant [[Stan Joplin]] had previously coached at [[Toledo Rockets men's basketball|Toledo]] until he was let go following the [[2007â08 NCAA Division I men's basketball season|2007â08 season]].<ref>[http://msuspartans.cstv.com/sports/m-baskbl/mtt/izzo_tom00.html Player Bio: Tom Izzo :: Men's Basketball<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
